properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 1:57AM CST until January 11 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...COMPLEX WINTER STORM WILL CONTINUE TO IMPACT THE REGION...

* WHAT...For the Winter Storm Warning, heavy snow expected this
afternoon and night. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 5 inches.
Winds gusting as high as 50 mph, especially near the lakeshore.
For the Winter Weather Advisory, mixed precipitation becoming
freezing drizzle this morning. Additional snow accumulations of
up to one tenth of an inch and ice accumulations of up to one
tenth of an inch. Winds gusting as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...Sheboygan County.

* WHEN...For the Winter Storm Warning, from 3 PM this afternoon
to 6 AM CST Sunday. For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 3
PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Patchy blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty winds could bring
down tree branches.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
